==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Madame Tussaud'''

# [[w:Marie Tussaud|Marie Tussaud]] (1761-1850), known for scuplting human figures in wax.

==== Quotations ====

*'''1885''' — [[w:Gilbert and Sullivan|Gilbert & Sullivan]], ''[[s:The_Mikado|The Mikado]]''
*:The amateur tenor, whose vocal villainies
*:All desire to shirk,
*:Shall during off-hours,
*:Exhibit his powers
*:To '''Madame Tussaud's''' waxwork.

